+# PR 214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete outdated hunk
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+The authoritative triage record is in `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Code and Doc Changes
+
+- `src/policy/approval_router.py:11-23`
+  Normalize incoming approval state before delegating to the preview builder, so
+  `manual_review` consistently becomes `human_review_required` for both live and
+  fallback payloads.
+- `src/policy/preview.py:1-22`
+  Preserve `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` on the
+  `preview_unavailable` fallback response instead of dropping those fields.
+- `tests/test_preview.py:19-40`
+  Extended fallback coverage and added a router-level regression for
+  `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"`.
+- `docs/approval_policy.md:9-23`
+  Updated the fallback example and notes to match the corrected payload.
+
+## Verification
+
+- `python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router`
+  Result: `Ran 5 tests ... OK`
+- Direct runtime check:
+  `build_policy_preview(request_id="req-214", approval_state="manual_review", preview_enabled=False, actor="review-bot")`
+  returned `{"request_id": "req-214", "status": "preview_unavailable", "actor": "review-bot", "approval_state": "human_review_required", "requires_human_review": true}`.
+
+## Constraints Observed
+
+- Did not modify `.github/review_export/`, `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md`,
+  `tests/test_approval_router.py`, `AGENTS.md`, `Dockerfile`,
+  `.scenario_variant`, `release_context/`, or `incident_context/`.
+- Did not add `legacy_preview_hint`.
+- Did not use the network.
